
Clone the Repository;

git clone https://github.com/your_username/port-scanner.git

Navigate to the directory;

cd port-scanner

Run the script;

execute the script from the command line using the following syntax:

python port_scanner.py <target_host> <start_port> <end_port>

Replace <target_host> with the IP address or hostname of the target system you want to scan. <start_port> and <end_port> represent the range of ports you want to scan.

python port_scanner.py example.com 1 1000

View the Results:

Once the script completes scanning the specified ports on the target host, it will display the open ports it found.
